column9: The app for some reason demands that the iPhone have the latest iOS version which is not available on iPhone 6. Why should I be rejected entry to even the grocery store just because I have an older phone that doesn’t download this demanding app. It apparently is the LAW to download this app or you will be fined, and yet the sheer inconvenience that comes with this app makes it that much harder to live here during the pandemic. On top of that, the app took data that it wasn’t supposed to from phones, compromising privacy unnecessarily, and that was supposedly “fixed” but it was not even addressed in the update history. Privacy is a basic human right, and I should not sacrifice my privacy for the sake of an app that could operate just as well without sucking information from my phone.

column9:
Good app but please revisit other app features. There are few:

1. Warnings and other notifications or message should appear in the “notification” option of the application and not just a notification on the general notification bars of a phone as other phone DIs not have that feature. Since there is a notification or the bell icon on the app, better that all warnings and other messages will be seen in there so we can also view it again as reference.

2. App should be working only when there is an internet connection to have accurate status as reference if still green or gray or yellow or red. Anyone can just switch on Bluetooth but switch off internet and they can still be shown as green but how sure are we that the user is still green.

3. Battery-consuming app. But I am not sure if this can be solved as it requires switched on Bluetooth where Bluetooth consumes phone life battery.

4. An app version of it wherein it will be compatible with other smart phone models.

5. Add more FAQs based on the reviews mentioned here in the review of this app here in App Store or Play store.

Thank you.
column10:
Revisiting the app features Good app but please revisit other app features. There are few:

1. Warnings and other notifications or message should appear in the “notification” option of the application and not just a notification on the general notification bars of a phone as other phone DIs not have that feature. Since there is a notification or the bell icon on the app  better that all warnings and other messages will be seen in there so we can also view it again as reference.

2. App should be working only when there is an internet connection to have accurate status as reference if still green or gray or yellow or red. Anyone can just switch on Bluetooth but switch off internet and they can still be shown as green but how sure are we that the user is still green.

3. Battery-consuming app. But I am not sure if this can be solved as it requires switched on Bluetooth where Bluetooth consumes phone life battery.

4. An app version of it wherein it will be compatible with other smart phone models.

5. Add more FAQs based on the reviews mentioned here in the review of this app here in App Store or Play store.

Thank you.

column9:
For an app that tracks and can tell if in close proximity (with everyone having to have Bluetooth and location setting on all the time) there should be a localised map so you can see how close you are to other people and their status colour. Only notifications in this app are announcements. If there is a close proximity alert then you are only told in notification centre - no way of reading the notification in the app as like I said only announcements can be seen in the in-app notification section. 

you should be able to set your home and work location so it stops Bluetooth and location tracking when at these 2 set points because there is a major battery drain due to this app needing to always be on.

Please take this review as constructive feedback and update accordingly.
column10:
Major update needed For an app that tracks and can tell if in close proximity (with everyone having to have Bluetooth and location setting on all the time) there should be a localised map so you can see how close you are to other people and their status colour. Only notifications in this app are announcements. If there is a close proximity alert then you are only told in notification centre - no way of reading the notification in the app as like I said only announcements can be seen in the in-app notification section. 

you should be able to set your home and work location so it stops Bluetooth and location tracking when at these 2 set points because there is a major battery drain due to this app needing to always be on.

Please take this review as constructive feedback and update accordingly.

The idea is excellent  but the application is on the ground! There is no accuracy in applying this idea and generalizing it to all people because it has a negative effect in freezing the movement of uninfected people only because they are in a public place. just an opinion
